  {
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Shower thought after chatting with <@U013ZLJARC7>: we delay teaching kids geometry until we can trust them not to poke someone's eye out with the pointy end of a compass.\n\nHere's a little program to do compass-and-straightedge geometrical construction on a computer: <https://gist.github.com/akkartik/20a0c7e7589c6179666fc78bc04b28b4>\n\nPictured below: constructing a second line (in black) parallel to a given line (red) passing through a given point.",
    "files": [
