              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ": we delay teaching kids geometry until we can trust them not to poke someone's eye out with the pointy end of a compass.\n\nHere's a little program to do compass-and-straightedge geometrical construction on a computer: "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://gist.github.com/akkartik/20a0c7e7589c6179666fc78bc04b28b4"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nPictured below: constructing a second line (in black) parallel to a given line (red) passing through a given point."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
